reviews: Excellent stay in Paris near the Gare de l'Est & Gare du Nord Train Stations. Easy metro station with ticket machines & attendant for tickets/ help across the street from the hotel. Exceptionally friendly & helpful staff. Very clean hotel! Spacious & well planned rooms for a stay in Paris along with comfortable bed & pillows. Loved the bar soup grinders in the bathrooms. Breakfast has a nice spread of choice in a comfortable sunny room or outdoor garden patio. Secure luggage hold room while you are checked in for your stay or even after check out before leaving the city. Safe neighborhood with restaurants, bakeries & shops nearby. Street noise is typical with traffic & loud people. Bring earplugs if needed. After many visits to Paris, this was one of our best stays within the city at a reasonable price.

Good location close to metro station Louis Blanc (line 7) and within walking distance of Gare du Nord station (12 mins). The room and bed were comfortable, we were overlooking the garden and found it nice and airy. We added on breakfast in the morning, 12€ pp, which was good. The only downside was the greeting we had when we arrived. The man at reception was a bit cold and overall it did not feel like a warm or genuine welcome - felt like we were disturbing him. Other than that, a good stay.

Very comfortable hotel with friendly, helpful staff. The location was great, with easy metro access to the main tourist sites, and numerous good restaurants and cafés in the local area as well as access to the canal (great for a morning run).

Chose this hotel on price…which appeared very reasonable for Paris. Location is very good with metro just across the road and some lovely walks and restaurants within short walking distance such as the Canal St Martin and the Parc Des Buttes Chaumont. We especially liked L’atmoshere bistro.
The room was very comfortable and breakfast (continental) good and a very reasonable price ( great for fuelling up for the day). The hotel staff were always friendly and helpful, including Reception and the ladies at breakfast time.
The only thing we didn’t like was stepping in and out of the bath for the shower, which didn’t feel altogether safe. I would suggest a non-slip mat, but this might have been just our particular bathroom, and wouldn’t prevent a future visit.
This was our first hotel visit in Paris, so I can’t compare to other similarly priced hotels, but sense from other reviews it offers very good value.

Good hotel in a beautiful part of the town. Clean room, good bed. We had a nice time and good privacy. In the neigbourhood are nice shops, 10 minutes walking from the trainstations Gare du Nord and Gare de l’Est.

This is the only one of many budget priced hotels that I would return to when next planning a trip to Paris. My wife has severe mobility problems and normally hotel washing/showering facilities make it very difficult, and often impossible. Our HLB wet room was the result of a lot of thought and it made it much easier for my wife to wash herself safely. Our room, though small, was clean and comfortable and all the staff were pleasant and helpful.
We were very satisfied with the choices for breakfast and were grateful to the young lady from the Dominican Republic who was particularly sociable and attentive to our needs.

Perfectly located near Metro and train station with all necessary very near: restaurants, supermarkets, transports, shops, etc. Very nice and friendly staff. The Hotel has everything for a nice stay. Would love to come back

Nice. good breakfast and reception service.
Thank you. Towels and bedding is in the prime included. Shampoo for hairs and body is in the bathroom. next by the metro is the hotel, is very nice for traveling to sightseen. We have had buy all day Ticket for metro, one for 8, 45 eur.

Great well located hotel with exceptionally friendly staff. Great value for money and surrounded by great bars and shops and the very easily located Louis blanc metro. Slightly disappointed about building work but at the end the new breakfast room made up for the slight inconvenience. I would highly recommend.

Good location near to both east & north stations . Our room on the first floor had just been re furnished and the whole room and bathroom was spotlessly clean . Lovely bouncy pillows and new crisp bedding .
Thank you good value

Hotel clean & very well maintained room was clean & fresh, staff are amazing very helpful the metro across the road is most helpful getting you to all the sights. Highly recommend the stay. All shop amenities right next door aswel as cafe/bars eateries.

This is a nice, affordable hotel in central Paris.
It’s very well located, 1 minute from Louis Blanc metro station.
The room was clean and pleasant.
Unfortunately it’s located right next to the police station so it’s quite loud with sirens during the day, but it doesn’t stay quiet at night.

I got my iPad stolen at the hotel. I left in the morning to see the city, and when I came back later someone had broken into my room and stolen it.

When I told the reception what happened they were very unsupportive and told me conflicting information. In the end, they asked me to file a complaint at a police station, which according to them was needed for an insurance request.

I filed the complaint and sent it to them. That was four months ago, and I still don't know who stole my iPad and still have not received any kind of compensation for what happened. When I ask the hotel manager for updates, she instructs me to contact the insurance company directly. When I contact the insurance company, they ignore my emails. A total mess.

I hope this unpleasant situation will be solved soon.

Friendly & helpful front of house staff: very clean, comfortable & quiet room. Great value for money. A good 10 minute walk from train station, but Metro across the road which takes you straight to the Louvre.

Hotel really clean and in front of the metro station. The personnel is very polite and available for any requests.
The room was really quiet and the bed was very comfortable.
The hotel is near Canal St. Martin, which is full of pubs and restaurants.

Great location directly opposite metro Louis blanc. Clean, comfortable and very helpful and polite staff. Would definitely stay here again. Highly recommend the lovely boulangerie across the road - amazing pastries and lunch, les lupins bistro which was a 10 minute walk away and Aspic restaurant for amazing food. Everything is within walking distance and Gare du Nord is about 10 minutes.

Everything was clean and comfy, breakfast was okay, just okay because everyday is the same, rooms and stuff great and friendly, would recommend for sure. Price is also really relatable with breakfast.

Great for a short stay, just next to a Line 7 Metro Station, parking was available in the hotelgarage ( not too expensive) Staff was extremely helpful and friendly.
Only downside was that we heard in our room at night always a humming sound that was apparently originating from the elevator going up and down.

Excelent hotel clean hotel with irony posters!
Very near for Gare du Nord, rue Lafayette will bring you to the center.
Even small repair works didn't bother at all. Helpful staff
Strongly recommended.

The room was lovely, clean, new, the staff was warm, friendly and attentive, and went an extra mile to get the room early ready. The only problem is that the room was quite cold, despite the heating at the max. But they kindly provided extra blankets when we asked.

Clean, modern & comfortable
The female receptionists were amazing and went out of there way to help us when we asked for it. The guy was just as efficient but didn’t quite have the same smiley customer service that makes all the difference.
Perfect location, seconds from the metro. We loved the bakery and fruit stall across the road so couldn’t comment on breakfast.
Perfect base, we would definitely return.

The room was small, but we knew it. The bed was comfortable and a lot of choice of pillows, which was nice! The staff were friendly and helpful.
The only negative comment is on the paper cups in the room, they are super small! Would be great to have proper cups!
Also, the breakfast selection should be changed every day or every second day. We had it all same for three mornings in a row, which was slightly disappointing, but still ok. If it would have been for more mornings, it would have been difficult! So more variety of French cuisine in different mornings would be a great bonus!

Booking in ran smoothly with an offer of hairdryer if required. A map of the area was also provided. The reception area was warm and welcoming with Christmas tree and small wrapped sweets 😋 in a glass jar. Love the extra touch. Excellent staff day and night. Metro almost a step out the door too.

The room was modern and very clean with kettle (yay!!!) Cleaned every day. We stayed for 4 nights. Great breakfast selection (hot and cold). Very happy we chose this hotel. Merci xx

Best location in respect to the metro station, literally cross the road. The area is a bit rough but not dangerous at all. Rooms are new, nice and clean, breakfast is good quality, rich and various. Personnel at reception very kind and friendly. I had a little problem with my daughter, had to call the doctor in the middle of the night, the guy at the reception was ever so helpful. Recommended

We had a very nice stay. The hotel was very clean. The receptionist was very helpfull and kind in arranging a parking spot at the hotel. Good location en nearby a metro station. Very much recommended for a stay in Paris.

Staff were very friendly! Perfect location right next to metro, rooms were very clean and a perfect size. Staff were always around to give help when needed. Check in process was simple and quick. Would definitely recommend for couples or an alone trip!

Very clean, friendly staff, breakfast is perhaps slightly overpriced though you do got plenty of options. we got clean towels and there was no excessive dust which was just amazing as I have a dust allergy. Location is also ideal next to the metro stop.

Good location, friendly staff, room and bathroom is rather small, but is completely renovated. We had a very quit room with vieuw on the inner garden. Perfect if you want to sleep with open window. No noise and good bed quality as well.

The room is very clean. The metro is just across the road from the hotel, which you can take to the different places of interest. There are many restaurants near by as well. I could even get food at 10pm in the night.

Great hotel and very friendly staff. Excellent value for money. The room was well equipped and sufficient for my stay. Breakfast was rich and delicious.
I’ll definitely choose it again when I come back to Paris.

Great, clean centrally located hotel. Just a 10 mins walk from Garre du Nord train station. Plenty of nice shops, restaurants and bars around.
Very friendly personeel and clean room.
I was allowed to check in earlier which I was very happy about.

The staff of the hotel was very nice and very helpful.The room was clean,warm and cosy.Comfortable bed.Place for our suitcases in the room.Bathroom was light and clean.Smiley housekeeping. Just short walk to Gare du Nord so it's very convenient.Also just 15 mins walk to the beautiful Montmartre:) Me and my fiance for sure would stay here again :)

Got a last minute booking at this great little hotel, as our pre-booked accommodation with another provider let us down. Clean, comfortable room, friendly, helpful staff and a great location within walking distance of Gare de L'Est and Gare du Nord and the Canal area. Metro also on the doorstep. Would thoroughly recommend.

This hotel is a great place to stay. The rooms are small but beautifully clean and have up-to-date plumbing and lighting, and tea making facilities in the rooms. Breakfast is very nice with lovely fresh pastries and bread, fruit, cold meats and cheese, hot bacon and eggs, The location is good, within walking distance of the Gare du Nord and Gare de l'Est, with Louis Blanc metro station just across the road. The nearby streets have lovely restaurants. The staff are especially nice, friendly and helpful.

This hotel is an absolute gem of a place. We stayed 3 nights, and we both really enjoyed our stay here. The room was immaculately clean, as was the bathroom (both cleaned daily with a towel change). It's a great base for sightseeing as you have the choice of 2 metro lines a 3-minute walk for the hotel that take you off to whether you need to go. The breakfast service had a great selection and kept us going way past lunchtime. It's a continental breakfast but with an excellent selection on offer and all fresh. We loved the scrambled eggs! The staff were extremely helpful and polite from the front desk staff to the cleaning staff. The hotel is located on a really small junction which at rush hour can sound a little noisy but hey, its Paris, embrace the atmosphere! We stayed on the 3rd floor and our room had double glazing so it really didn't bother us. We would absolutely stay here again.

My fiance and I had a great time in the Louis Blanc hotel! The staff was very friendly and gave us a lot of recommendations! The main benefit of the hotel is its location, which allows you to discover Paris by foot and has a metro station 10m away and the beautiful canal St-Martin nearby!

We really enjoyed the stay at this hotel. Very cute and comfortable place to stay. Super clean and we loved the soaps they provided. Very friendly staff and close to everything. There is a metro station right behind and great restaurants and groceries around it. The train station is just a few blocks from there. We loved everything about this hotel, we definitely want to go back.

The room was basic, good size and a walk in shower but it was really hot (they'd switched off the air con) and so noisy as the walls are paper thin.
We were on the third floor by the lift and opposite a cupboard the staff used. Every morning we were woken up by staff banging the cupboard door repeatedly, traffic noise and people talking loudly. We asked to move but were told there were no quiet rooms available.
The shower pressure was weak but it was a nice size cubicle.
I wouldn't stay again, expecially if I wanted a relaxing break and a sleep in.

Very nice hotel with friendly staf. About 12 minutes walk from Gare du Nord, for me that was important. The rooms are clean, comfortable beds, metrostation across the road. I will recommend this hotel to anyone.

Hôtel in off the beaten path of Paris. We got a room on the 1st floor and thought that it would be as noisy at night as it was during the day but it was not. Room is European size and clean. Staff is very helpful in every way. Breakfast has a large variety of food and beverage and is excellent. There is also a nice interior garden with patio chairs and tables where you could not hear the noise of the city. It was very relaxing. This is a good place if you do not mind being a bit away from the bustle and hustle of the city.

Firstly - location is excellent right next to metro access to town nice and easy. The neighbourhood is bustling and only a 10 min walk from Gare Du Nord so save some pennies and walk to your hotel.

Bring earplugs just in case got room overlooking street as we had and you’ll be fine- glazing is good it does help with street noise.

Cheaper to eat out locally obviously than in town- nice couple of restaurants we tried near the canal one was Eritrean and the other Thai. Around £12 for a main. Check trip advisor.

Room- we were given room 105. Have to admit little disappointed as it was dated, mattress wasn’t very comfortable I could feel springs and it really needs a refresh. However, had a little kettle was immaculately clean, tv. So very basic but clean.

Service- excellent. Polite staff, accommodated our needs with meds needing to be stored in fridge for my husband.

Food- breakfast was good. Very good choice- cold meats, cheese, yoghurts, cereal, breads, eggs to do to your own softness, hot drinks, fresh juice, fruits. Breakfast room kept lovely and clean. Nice little outside area we enjoyed starting our day here- was starting to get little chilly in mid sept but we wanted to eat out as much as we could.

Hotel could improve by 1- clamping down on guests obviously smoking in rooms- this is very dangerous and they just need smoke alarms fitting in room to discourage this along with a designated smoking around outside the hotel. Never had this issue in any other hotel and it was disconcerting to say the least as I was immediately aware this put all guests and staff at risk in event someone left cigarette burning by accident at night.

2 - upgrade beds in our room (105) and redecorate remaining rooms that need upgrading as this lets down the hotel as everywhere else is pleasant and modern to walk around. Suspect entire corridor was like this as corridor felt a bit old fashioned and dated with strong smell of cigarette smoke too.

Excellent location! First day I had room with the door attached to other room. I didn't feel comfortable. Next day they changed that room. Mid night attendant (bearded guy) was amazing person with very good service. I didn't like the tallest attendant. I think he is manager and he was very rude. Ac was not good enough. But was ok.

We checked in at midnight after flying half way across the world. In 30 minutes had killed multiple insects and were utterly disgusted with the burns in the carpet and dirty walls. Wouldn’t refund us.

Staff were friendly. Rooms clean and newly decorated. Room change given on request as booked a double bed. Nothing was too. Much trouble. Near to tube station with excellent connections. Close-to eurotunnel station. Breakfast suitable

Firstly the positives: the bed was very comfy, and the staff were extremely polite and hospitable. The teas and coffee provisions were satisfactory also.

However there were two concerns with our visit. The first was that there was a lot of noise at night inside the hotel room. There was noise outside, especially from sirens. However this was not a major issue. Unfortunately there was a whirring noise 24/7 coming from inside the hotel, even with the air con turned off. This was a disturbance getting to sleep, for which we were unable to do anything about.

The second concern was that the hotel breakfast was not particularly hygienic. The hotel doors were open into the garden, which meant that there were bugs (such as flies) coming into the area where the food was. Unfortunately there was uncovered food, such as croissants and salami, which was attracting these insects. These food should have been either covered in cling film, or stored in a tub of some sort.

We had a lovely visit to Paris and stay at the Louis Blanc
Clean and fresh with air conditioning and wonderfully comfortable beds after plenty of walking around and doing touristy things .
1 minute walk from metro and perfect location to just wander around and enjoy cafe culture and soak up atmosphere
Staff very pleasant and helpful
One downside is we booked two rooms and paid an extra £43.00 for one of the rooms with a bath as my husband likes a soak to relax his back . This was a mistake as the bath was half size and he could not fit in it as he is over 6 ft so it just became an impossibly tight shower .
In England I would have asked for this money to be refunded but unfortunately my French is not adequate enough to discuss this
Please do not let this put you off the hotel is lovely

Nice clean hotel in an area with lots of restaurants and public transport nearby. Staff is very friendly and open to answer questions. When we had a question about a restaurant, the guy at the reception called them for us. Good service!

Great hotel, size of room you would expect for such a good price, booked direct and got a better deal than any booking site, easy online check in , all staff were very friendly , good size bed , balcony, excellent air con, room tidied bed linen and towels changed every day, 50 meters from metro,brilliant bakery opposite, supermarket 50 meters and 200 meters from the vibrant canal district with great bars and restaurants. A really good base will definitely come back if we can have the same room !!
I do get some people may not have had the same experience dependent on where they room was in the hotel but I can only describe our great stay.

Modern design, helpful staff. Rooms modern but small. Wet room large and lovely and clean. Location great, opposite Metro with some nice restaurants, bakery and fruit shops within 50 m. Air con really useful in heat of the summer

Excellent hotel and lovely staff. Friendly, subway, clean, good breakfast, good location, silence, not expensive, good rooms. We will come back as soon as possible. 20 minutes walk from Gare du Nord station.

Good stay for a good price. Nice hotel, good service and a nice room. Location is also very good. Your really close to al the attractions. Would recommend if you are looking for a hotel that isn’t expensive.

Hotel is in an ideal location, being only a 15 minute walk from Gare Du Nord station and having a metro station just across the street. Also plenty of shops and two very pleasant bistros / bars within a shot walk which we visited. Hotel room was very clean and had everything we needed for our stay. Continental breakfast was also very good particularly with the option to sit in the courtyard garden. Hotel staff were all very friendly and attentive and happy to provide any assistance or advice during our stay. Would highly recommend and would definitely consider returning for a further visit.

Really lovely staff at reception, friendly and knowledgeable.
Great location to explore Paris with 2 metro stations on your doorstep.
Interesting area with all local amenities close by.
Highly recommended.

This hotel was a comfortable stay close to the metro. We had everything we needed for the amount of time we stayed in the room as we were out most of the day. The staff were welcoming and helpful.
I would recommend this hotel!

Great position, only short walk from Gare du Nord station. Metro station just outside hotel, very handy for exploring Paris. Very courteous staff, good comfortable room with air conditioning. Very good continental breakfast. Will visit again.

The location is very good, close to the metro and public transport, they also have underground parking. Bright and clean rooms, nice staff, tasty breakfast, a big plus is that they accept pets. We rested very well, I recommend this hotel.

A tale of 2 halves…..

I had previously contacted the hotel to request rooms close together (teen kids travelling with us but I need them close to me in a strange city!).

On arrival (4pm) only 1 of 3 rooms was ready. We waited and we’re shown to the first room. Clean, nicely updated.

We were then Told room 2 was ready. On another floor - not a problem as a room for adults. Again nicely presented.

Third room - there was ‘a problem’. Heart sank immediately. This was half hour after check in.

‘No more updated rooms available’.

‘This room is ok, but it hasn’t been updated’

This is not what you want to hear from hotel reception staff after a long day travelling.

This room was 2 floors away from our children!!

After a lot of talking (being told ‘I’m sorry, I understand but there is nothing I can do),
time and some mum anxiety tears, we eventually spoke to the manager who (somewhat miraculously) found us a room right Next door to our children! A Christmas miracle…..?

Anyway, the rest of the stay was pleasant and the rooms were comfortable & clean……

Nb…room service only seemed to
Happen late pm (around 4)……..which seemed
Crazy to us as people return to hotel around that time after a day sightseeing to have a
Clean up before going out for dinner?

I suppose you get what you pay for. Not the best service. The complimentary coffee was finished and we had to buy coffee in the cafeteria for 4€ instead, not even real coffee, just one of those machines where you press a button for cappuccino. We hadn’t ordered any room service but the personnel had gotten a room number wrong and walked in on us more or less naked. Otherwise quite fresh rooms. Good cleaning. Nice bed.

We only used the room facilities - no breakfast, etc - and booked with a deal from Eurostar. It's a very basic room but suited our needs to be close to the station, easy to get around Paris from. Clean, and was freshly changed during our 2 night stay. An easy bolt-hole.

We have enjoyed our stay in this hotel. Very clean rooms, good breakfast and located in an area with lots of bars and restaurants.
Will certainly come back to this hotel when visiting Paris next time.

I had an amazing experience. I was travelling with my small daughter. Easy to find. Walking distance from Gare du Nord. Staff was courteous, welcoming and helpful. They gave promptly all the information about the local area and the public transport. They gave us a local map, a Paris map and all the answers before we ask for anything. The room was clean. We could leave our luggage before the check in time and after the check out.

The hotel is very easy to find as it's not far from Louis Blanc metro. The garden room is gorgeous. The breakfast is a buffet feast with everything you could want from juices, hot drinks, cold meats, cheeses, breads, pastries, yogurts and cereals. The rooms were a good size with tea and coffee making facilities.
The only issue we had was the rooms were not ready at check in. But given the positives and late checkout it's not a big deal.

We had a fantastic stay and can't wait to return.

11pm. Landed, missed the last train so took the bus.

2am arrived at prepaid hotel

There had been a water leak. The night manager said he would find us another room in a different hotel.

2:30 to 3:30 he calls hotels. Then asks us to look for rooms.

I found a room, €600 for the night. I handed the phone to the night manager. Spoke, hung up. “Sorry, too expensive, Manager would not allow that”.

4am. He has found a room. Books us a taxi, Asks us to pay and we will be reimbursed

Travel 30 mins across Paris to Hotel Paris Vaugirard. The night manager was pleasant, offered us a drink and had the keys on the counter ready

10am, wake up, breakfast, check out.
One of the receptionists asks another if we need to pay. Clueless but we did not have to pay

12:30. Check in at Hotel Paris Louis Blanc, hand over the taxi receipts totalling €65.

At checkout I was told the compensation and taxi’s could not be resolved but I could leave my contact details and they will be in touch.

No one contacted me.
Emailed them 1 week later and was offered the money for the taxis. I provided bank details and asked about further compensation.

The response, “on your next stay we will give you complimentary breakfast and a discount”

I responded to thay email saying the compensation was insulting and asked for some monetary value.

It has been 2 weeks, no response and we have not received the money for the taxis.

When I checked into the room, I noticed that there was an unpleasant smell in the room. I went to reception and described my problem. The staff (sorry can't remember his name) was very helpful and friendly and offered me another room without much hesitation.
I am really happy and super satisfied with the service and flexibility.

SIMPLY THANK YOU

Staff were v friendly and helpful. Bed comfortable and good size. Bathroom was good, water pressure not great but would not put us off coming back.

Did not have breakfast but cafe area looked nice.

Small balcony gave was a nice bonus on 5th floor

The hotel is very clean, modern and nice. It’s situated in less then 100 meters from the metro station where you can go to the city center in a very few minutes. Definitely recommend for a 2-3 days vacation in Paris. Lot of restaurants in the areas

Good:
- near to Gare Nord
- very near to Metro
- lovely little garden
- nice and clean room and bathroom
- perfect bed (not too soft)

Not good:
- very loud at night
- no alternative Milk (soja or almond) at the breakfast

Had a great stay here thankyou. Booked as a Eurostar package. Lovely helpful receptionist Hana. Room was bright, very clean and serviced daily by friendly housekeeping. Comfy large bed. Nice garden to sit out in. Great location 10 minute walk from Gar du Nord and across road from Metro for easy access to Paris city centre. Lovely pizzeria and delicious bakery opposite. Supermarket and couple of restaurant/bars close by. Close to Canal St Martin for more restaurant/bars.

i would like to make a complaint about the reception. i've come here to stay on holiday with my family, and i have noticed that the receptionists are extremely rude. they are not friendly with my kids at all, they have no respect and they leave the building unattended without any staff. The room that we are in is extremely small for 4 people staying here, and this has caused inconvenience for me and my family. we do not feel welcome at all. Sometimes when we leave the room and the cleaners come and clean, we come back and there are things missing from our personal belongings, not to mention the cleaners not cleaning the room properly. The receptionists complain about my kids making noise, yet they allow customers to bring their pets to the hotel, so i don't see what the problem is. i have never felt soo experienced such violation during a stay at a hotel, taking into consideration that this is my first time here, and they are treating us like this. They seem to not have any training skills on how to satisfy their customers and how to treat them with respect, and this has risen concer to me, because it seems like they don't know how to do their job right.

HPLB HOTEL, PARIS LOUIS BLANC , 232 RUE DUFAUBOURG SAINT MARTIN LOUISBLANC.

- please guys do not waste your money to come here unless you want to be treated like rubbish.

After reading positive reviews we settled on this hotel for our budget two night stay in Paris. We booked it as part of a Eurostar package. There were so many things we liked about the hotel - just 10min walk from Gare du Nord, clean facilities, nice hot shower, friendly and attentive staff and lovely courtyard garden to enjoy the decent breakfast. I've stayed at expensive business orientated hotels that in substance did not offer much more. Will definitely stay there again if the deal is right.

We have a very nice stay at this hotel. Everything was nice and clean, good beds, good shower, great service. Breakfast was good. Hotel is well situated just a few metres from the Metro Station. I would definitely recommend.

We had a great stay at this hotel. Everything was nice and clean, good beds, good shower, great service and the garden is an extra plus!
Location is perfect; near Gare du Nord and a subwaystation across the street. We didn’t book breakfast, but there’s a small bakery across the street with delicious food. There’s also a supermarket around the corner.

Only small negative thing is there was no fridge in the room. We bought some drinks, but couldn’t keep them cool.

Traveled with my ten year old son.
We were lucky enough to have a room with a king-size bed (room 218)
The room was clean and quite spacious for a Paris hotel room.

The bath was not full size, not that this was an issue. The shower was clean, powerful and they supplied bodywash/shampoo.

We arrived quite late and there was a lovely Asian man who assisted us with our needs, he again assisted us with our requests on the second night. Very friendly and helpful, definitely sells the hotel when the staff are nice.

The staff at this hotel were all very friendly and pleasent, other hotels in Paris this has not been a luxury.

I'd definitely stay here again.
The metro is literally outside the door with the pink line taking you right into the action.

You are also within walking distance to the large station of gare deu Nord

It's worth noting that I was unaware when I booked with Agoda that breakfast was included, we missed breakfast on day one but had it on day two. The breakfast was decent enough, my kid was happy with the options, they had a very cute courtyard you could eat in too.

I would definitely recommend.

Hotel is well situated just a few metres from the Metro Station. Room was cleaned every day. Breakfast was good and was restocked on a regular basis. Staff were friendly and helpful, Only slight drawback is that the metro line by the hotel is not on the same line as the Gare du Nord. There is a bus service that takes about 5 minutes. Overall well recommended.

Easygoing, super clean and nice hotel. Perfect, value for your money. Close to Metro access. Daily room clean up and fresh towels, friendly helpful staff. Nice breakfast restaurants and bakery around the corner.

We got this hotel in a package from Eurostar, after looking at trip advisor pictures and reviews we were happy to stay here as looked very pleasant. The hotel lobby and reception was lovely and made us look forward to seeing our room. Our room was incredibly basic, very small and the bed was the smallest double bed I’ve ever seen. The room was just missing basic commodities like a mirror in the bedroom, a bin in the room and plugs next to the bed. Simple things but also things you do expect from a hotel. We also got back to our room at about 5/5:30 to get ready to go out again, the chamber maid was in the corridor and when we went into our room the room hadn’t even been cleaned yet , you’d think this would be done whilst you’re out and about! Although despite these we did have a comfortable stay and the location was right next to a metro line taking you straight into the centre. As well, we were able to leave our bags with the hotel before and after checking in and out which was very helpful! I would recommend to people needing a simple room to stay in for their time in Paris

The room was just big enough to get in to. There was mold on the bathroom walls and if you use the toilet you had to sit with your knees against the opposing wall. The fellow in reception tried to make the most of it; hee was very helpful but it didn’t change the room. We abandoned the room first thing in the morning and stayed in the heart of Paris at hotel de La Paix Eiffel in Rm #4. Had a patio and a roomier room. Walking distance to the Eiffel Tower. The Louis Blanc was quite far from the heart of Paris.

Everything good! The room is clean and the hotel is in a strategic place. The metro station is on the other side of the street, the line is the n° 7 well connected to the most relevant places (Louvre, Opéra, Champs Elysees).
The hotel staff was very nice!

Everything was perfekt.
The location was good near by the Metro. Perfekt to go and visiting everything in the city. The employer was very friendly at the rezeption.
The only negativ point the room was a little small

First the bad - which really more minor inconveniences - before the good. The standard double room is quite small and although online it said a hairdryer and safe were in the rooms we had to ask for a hairdryer from reception and the safe was there too. I’m vegan but there was no non-dairy milk at breakfast. They also don’t have an environmental policy of not changing towels unless requested. Toiletries are basic. However, the room was modern and quiet, with a comfortable bed and tea/coffee making facilities. WiFi is free and strong. The shower was good and breakfast was fine. The hotel is short (10-minute) walk from Gare I’d Nord and there is a metro station just across the road. Ideal for a short city break. I would come back.

A very good budget hotel near Canal Saint-Martin. Location is excellent. Louis Blanc metro station is around the corner. Train stations Gare du Nord and Gare de l’Est are within walking distance. The hotel is clean, modern and in good condition. The staff is friendly (mostly) and you can get along in English. The bed was good. In the bathroom there was a small bathtub, which was ok, but caution is advised when getting out of it. The street traffic noise can be disturbing, at least in the corner room. The breakfast is plain but it is quite all right. The thing we always wonder, is the lack of hangers and wall hooks. Two wall hooks in the bathroom, none in the hotel room and only 3 coat hangers. That is nothing less than scrubby for us two staying for 4 nights.

We stayed at the Louis Blanc hotel, on the site it looked good, with a very good breakfast, so we decided to book our rooms (3) in this hotel. I looked for a hotel with breakfast included. We were with a group of 7 persons and I booked 3 rooms with breakfast. Some days later a friend booked also (because they wanted to come with us) a room and breakfast.
When we checked in, there was no breakfast included and had we to pay 12 euro per person each day for breakfast. The information on booking.com is not good or they changed it after we booked. We were very disappointed.
Beside that the hotel was good, clean and very good located.

The location of the hotel isn‘t the best but the metro station is very close. The rooms are very small and the service by the receptionists could be better (e. g. be more friendly, give informations such as plan for the metro or map of the city). The cards for entering the rooms weren‘t prepared and we first were sent to the wrong room. So to sum up, it‘s a price

We needed a hotel for 2 nights in Paris after traveling through Loire Valley. The room was very clean, bed was comfortable and was quiet. The staff were friendly and helpful. We were also able to park our rental car in their garage for 20 euros a night. I was told I should let them know in advance for this but they fortunately had availability when we were there. The second night we stumbled on street parking overnight very near the hotel which is free from 8pm to 9am. This worked since we were leaving early the next day. There is also a fruit market and several pastry shops a few doors down. I would stay here again.

Nicely located close to Paris-Nord station, Louis Blance metro station accross the street. Some nice restaurants nearby, also a good supermarket around the corner.
Modern room, well sound-proofed.
Bathroom also modern, but quite small.
Nice breakfast, but it felt the breakfast room was understaffed. The staff barely managed to keep up, but did a good job and service was friendly.

Decent hotel with decent facilities. Underground parking garage is a huge plus, breakfast is good and the staff is pretty friendly. Room was slightly disappointing; not as modern as the photos would suggest. Stains on the carpet, otherwise clean. Fresh towels every day and an elevator, which was nice.
Location is great: right beside underground station Louis Blanc with easy access to the city centre. Unfortunately no safe in the room, but it's nice to be able to leave your luggage at the desk for a final day in the city before the journey home.
Oh, and check out time of twelve o'clock was great!

It was conveniently close to Gare du Nord and right opposite a metro station.
The rooms have been redone in 2021, and they're amazing. The quality of the bedding is impressive, no noice at night. We had two very restful nights.
The staff was super friendly, even my requests via email where positively and rapidly answered.

This is a very good hotel for a stay in Paris. The rooms are extremely clean and the service is very good as well. Also, you can reach everything by foot from here and there are nice cafés and bakeries in the area.

We stayed here for two nights, we had a really good time. The beds were incredibly comfortable and the bathroom looks like it was just renovated. Most importantly everything in our room was clean. Only downside was thin doors so you could hear the halls and another room was smoking which you could smell in our room.

I really liked this hotel! It was clean and very conveniently located next to a metro stop. There are lots of cheap and delicious restaurants all around. The people at the front desk were nice.

My only complaint is that they did not care about the “do not disturb” sign. Completely disregarded it for several days. It’s worth noting that we stayed for 10 days and had the sign up for most days except a few. They came in regardless. Also, there was no money safe.

Overall a good experience. I recommend it if you don’t mind the “do not disturb” thing.

Budget friendly? Check! Location? Check! Nice little room? Check! Friendly, accommodating and lovely attendants/workers? Triple check!!! I would definitely come back! If you’re not picky, this is perfect for you!

The hotel staff were all very nice and helpful. It was a nice and clean hotel with nice rooms and a very good location near a metro and bus stop. The breakfast was good, quite a lot of choice and I loved the apple juice :) I will return here, especially in summer because they have a very cute garden.

We stayed at the HPLB for a few days arriving from the US, and really enjoyed our stray. The metro station "Louis Blanc" is right around the corner, and the Gare de l'Est is a mere 5-10min away walking. There are a few commerces around, including a Franprix, a pharmacy and a bakery with delicious puff pastry!

We had an amazing experience! The woman at the receptioniste helped us very well with all the questions and our luggages. The rooms are very clean and nothing bad to say about it. The location is terrific, metro is 40 metres from the hotel. We had a good stay! :)

Very well located hotel, clean and quiet. Shops, restaurants and metro station just few steps away from the hotel. Great breakfast with croissants! :) Staff is kind and can speak English. Fully recommended.

A great stay..clean room, confortable bed and very good location near of everithing.
Towels changed everiday, bed was very confortable,the area was a bit noisy.
Great option for a 3 days trip
Lots of economic options to eat nearby

We were so happy with our choice to stay at Louis Blanc and really feel like it was great value for money. We read some mixed reviews so had our fingers crossed that it would be decent. We got a late flight so we arrived after 11pm. They request that you let them know if you will arrive after 11pm so we did this via their chat service and there was absolutely no issue with it and the gentleman who checked us in (Roger I think?) was really friendly and lovely. We were completely accommodated with our request for a quiet room, we were facing the garden and on the top floor so had no issues sleeping at all, we actually slept really well. There was maybe a couple of sirens throughout the day and as you'd expect in a busy city like Paris a wee bit of outside noise but this seemed to mostly stop mid evening time. The room was not massive but was a decent size and the bed was huge and really comfy which was amazing. The big bed meant there wasn't loads of room for furniture so there was just a small hanging space with a couple of hangers and shelf for your clothes but this was totally fine for us. There was also a desk with a chair, kettle and tea. The room and bed felt really clean and the room was cleaned every day with new towels provided and bed made. The bathroom was modern and clean with soap provided. The bathroom was on the small side and our knees were close to the wall when sitting on the toilet but I think most Paris hotels just have to make the most of their limited space, so although a little more bathroom space would have been nice it caused us no issue. The reception provided us with a hairdryer on request, they looked after our luggage after we checked out and put our food in their fridge when we requested. We didn't get the breakfast so couldn't comment on that. The subway station is also right outside so it was easy to explore paris by jumping on and off the metro with a day ticket. It is not the most central but still pretty central and at most maybe half an hour by metro to any sights, most sights are closer and some are in walking distance. We didn't explore the area much but there were bakers and small market shops next door and across the street and I can't say we ever felt unsafe there. We also found it easy to get to the hotel from Orly airport, we took a short trip on the Orlyval train and then a train from Antony station to Gare du Nord which is maybe a 10mim walk to the hotel but there were also lots of other transport you could take. Overall, clean hotel with a good bed in a decent location and with accommodating staff and amenities so thats all we needed. We were impressed with the hotel and really enjoyed out trip, thanks!

We had a very lovely stay at this hotel. The staff was helpful and we found the room clean, tidy and cosy, albeit slightly small. We also thoroughly enjoyed the breakfast and the location was great with a city-bound metro line just accross the street.
